            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Schuyler Colfax was a Republican member of the House of Representatives from Indiana (1855-69), Speaker of the House (1863-69), and Vice-President during Grant&#039;s first term. These letters, photostats from the Colfax Papers in the Library of Congress, discuss the election of Lincoln, the necessity for compromise, and the payment of senators.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


